			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, I'd be looking for a polynomial with as few terms as possible.<br /><br />With some help of Wikipedia, I found the polynomial x^n + x^31 + x^30 + x^10 + 1, and if my math is correct, that should be<br />11000000 00000000 00000100 00000001 = C0000401<br /><br />So, when a 1 is shifted out from an ASL, the variable is XORed with C0000401.<br /><br />I may be wrong though.<br /><br />C0000401 creates a lot of feedback, which requires a lot of extra XORs along with shifts. Perhaps a polynomial that begins with 00xxxxxx would be better.</div>

					
							<br /><br />
